      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GLADIATRIX (6) is a talented filly who resumes after winning six races up to G2 level as a juvenile. Broke when last seen in a G1 at Melton in December but she has won both previous fresh attempts and should be ready to go after winning her last three trials. DEEP LOVE NZ (3) is progressing well having worked but proven too tough at Bendigo last week. Led from this draw for an easy win at Menangle prior and could land the hat trick. IM HAVINTOTROT (4) was last seen when midfield in the Breeders Crown final at Melton in December and showed some ability prior, highlighted by a Maryborough win. Readied with three solid trials so can make a good return. A gap to the other two, debutant ET JULIETTE (2) may be the best of them.",
